# World VFX (Echo and Shared Paths)

## Iron Law

Any change to combat, abilities, spells, items, or moves that can show world VFX must call that VFX correctly for **both** Hero and Echo. Do not gate attack / jump / zap / MagicMissile / MissileSprite / operate / emitters on `ctx.heroFX` alone.

## Gate correctly

| Concern                                                                       | Gate                                                                                  |
| ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Attack, jump, zap, missiles, operate, emitters, hit sounds tied to those      | `UseContext.canWorldFx(ch)` / `ctx.canWorldFx()` (`sprite != null && parent != null`) |
| QuickSlot, GLog, identify, talent UI, `spendAndNext`, camera-only Hero riders | `ctx.heroFX`                                                                          |

```java
// ❌ BAD — Echo never swings / never bolts
if (ctx.heroFX && kit.sprite != null) {
	kit.sprite.attack(enemy.pos, doHit);
} else {
	doHit.call();
}

// ✅ GOOD — on-stage Echo shows VFX; headless still sync-applies
if (ctx.heroFX && UseContext.canWorldFx(kit)) {
	kit.sprite.attack(enemy.pos, doHit);
} else {
	if (UseContext.canWorldFx(kit)) {
		kit.sprite.attack(enemy.pos); // visual only; hit stays sync (borrow-safe)
	}
	doHit.call();
}
```

Relocates: use `Char.move(cell, false)` (or `ScrollOfTeleportation.appear`) so the sprite is placed — do not update `pos` alone.

## Prefer tests

When you change a path that has world VFX, add or extend a test that proves Echo fires it with a live parent:

- `EchoTestSupport.installEchoBossLevel` + `attachInstantProjectileParent(boss)`
- Assert recycles / stub counters: `magicMissileRecycles`, `missileSpriteRecycles`, `stubSpriteAttackCalls`, `stubSpriteJumpCalls`, `stubSpriteOperateCalls`, `stubSpriteZapCalls`, `stubSpritePlacedCell`

```java
// ✅ GOOD — Echo wand bolt actually recycles MagicMissile
EchoTestSupport.InstantProjectileGroup fx =
		EchoTestSupport.attachInstantProjectileParent(boss);
wand.zapAs(UseContext.echo(boss), player.pos);
Assertions.assertThat(fx.magicMissileRecycles).isGreaterThan(0);
```

Headless without a parent must still apply gameplay (damage, buffs, move) synchronously.

## Before finishing

- [ ] No new `heroFX && sprite…` world-VFX gates
- [ ] Echo on-stage path shows the same class of VFX as Hero
- [ ] Test asserts VFX when practical; otherwise note the gap
